#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.11:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.11:0.2"
msgid "2. Sīhanādavagga"
msgstr "2. The Lion’s Roar"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 11. Sīhanādasutta → sāriputtasīhanādasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Sīhanādasutta"
msgstr "11. Sāriputta’s Lion’s Roar"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.374"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "an9.11:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā "
"sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

msgctxt "an9.11:1.3"
msgid "“vuttho me, bhante, sāvatthiyaṃ vassāvāso."
msgstr "“Sir, I have completed the rainy season residence at Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "an9.11:1.4"
msgid "Icchāmahaṃ, bhante, janapadacārikaṃ pakkamitun”ti."
msgstr "I wish to depart to wander the countryside.”"

msgctxt "an9.11:1.5"
msgid "“Yassadāni tvaṃ, sāriputta, kālaṃ maññasī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, Sāriputta, go at your convenience.”"

msgctxt "an9.11:1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ "
"katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then Sāriputta got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the "
"Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving."

msgctxt "an9.11:1.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu acirapakkante āyasmante sāriputte bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"And then, not long after Sāriputta had left, a certain monk said to the "
"Buddha:"

msgctxt "an9.11:1.8"
msgid ""
"“āyasmā maṃ, bhante, sāriputto āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkanto”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, Venerable Sāriputta attacked me and left without saying sorry.”"

msgctxt "an9.11:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "So the Buddha said to a certain monk:"

msgctxt "an9.11:1.10"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena sāriputtaṃ āmantehi:"
msgstr "“Please, monk, in my name tell Sāriputta that"

msgctxt "an9.11:1.11"
msgid "‘satthā taṃ, āvuso sāriputta, āmantetī’”ti."
msgstr "the teacher summons him.”"

msgctxt "an9.11:1.12"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yenāyasmā sāriputto "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to Sāriputta and said to him:"

msgctxt "an9.11:1.13"
msgid "“satthā taṃ, āvuso sāriputta, āmantetī”ti."
msgstr "“Reverend Sāriputta, the teacher calls you.”"

msgctxt "an9.11:1.14"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā sāriputto tassa bhikkhuno paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” Sāriputta replied."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: mahāmoggallāno → mahāmoggalāno (mr)
#. VAR: avāpuraṇaṃ → apāpuraṇaṃ (s1-3, mr)
#. VAR: vihāre āhiṇḍanti → vihārena vihāraṃ anvāhiṇḍanti (bj, pts1) | vihāraṃ āhiṇḍanti (s1-3)
msgctxt "an9.11:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno āyasmā ca ānando avāpuraṇaṃ "
"ādāya vihāre āhiṇḍanti:"
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerables Mahāmoggallāna and Ānanda took a key and went "
"from dwelling to dwelling, saying:"

msgctxt "an9.11:2.2"
msgid "“abhikkamathāyasmanto, abhikkamathāyasmanto."
msgstr "“Come forth, venerables! Come forth, venerables!"

msgctxt "an9.11:2.3"
msgid "Idānāyasmā sāriputto bhagavato sammukhā sīhanādaṃ nadissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Now Venerable Sāriputta will roar his lion’s roar in the presence of the "
"Buddha!”"

msgctxt "an9.11:2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ "
"sāriputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one "
"side. The Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "an9.11:2.5"
msgid "“idha te, sāriputta, aññataro sabrahmacārī khīyanadhammaṃ āpanno:"
msgstr "“Sāriputta, one of your spiritual companions has made this complaint:"

msgctxt "an9.11:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘āyasmā maṃ, bhante, sāriputto āsajja appaṭinissajjacārikaṃ pakkanto’”ti."
msgstr "‘Venerable Sāriputta attacked me and left without saying sorry.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Yassa nūna, bhante, kāye kāyagatāsati anupaṭṭhitā assa, so idha aññataraṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkameyya."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, someone who had not established mindfulness of the body might well "
"attack one of their spiritual companions and leave without saying sorry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.375"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, pathaviyaṃ sucimpi nikkhipanti asucimpi nikkhipanti "
"gūthagatampi nikkhipanti muttagatampi nikkhipanti kheḷagatampi nikkhipanti "
"pubbagatampi nikkhipanti lohitagatampi nikkhipanti, na ca tena pathavī "
"aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose they were to toss both clean and unclean things on the earth, like "
"feces, urine, spit, pus, and blood. The earth isn’t horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted because of this."

msgctxt "an9.11:4.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, pathavīsamena cetasā viharāmi vipulena "
"mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I live with a heart like the earth, abundant, expansive, "
"limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an9.11:4.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa nūna, bhante, kāye kāyagatāsati anupaṭṭhitā assa, so idha aññataraṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkameyya. (1)"
msgstr ""
"Someone who had not established mindfulness of the body might well attack "
"one of their spiritual companions and leave without saying sorry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:5.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, āpasmiṃ sucimpi dhovanti asucimpi dhovanti gūthagatampi …"
" muttagatampi … kheḷagatampi … pubbagatampi … lohitagatampi dhovanti, na ca "
"tena āpo aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose they were to wash both clean and unclean things in water, like "
"feces, urine, spit, pus, and blood. The water isn’t horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted because of this. …"

msgctxt "an9.11:5.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, āposamena cetasā viharāmi vipulena mahaggatena "
"appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I live with a heart like water, abundant, expansive, "
"limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an9.11:5.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa nūna, bhante, kāye kāyagatāsati anupaṭṭhitā assa, so idha aññataraṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkameyya. (2)"
msgstr ""
"Someone who had not established mindfulness of the body might well attack "
"one of their spiritual companions and leave without saying sorry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:6.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, tejo sucimpi ḍahati asucimpi ḍahati gūthagatampi … "
"muttagatampi … kheḷagatampi … pubbagatampi … lohitagatampi ḍahati, na ca "
"tena tejo aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a fire was to burn both clean and unclean things, like feces, urine, "
"spit, pus, and blood. The fire isn’t horrified, repelled, and disgusted "
"because of this. …"

msgctxt "an9.11:6.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, tejosamena cetasā viharāmi vipulena mahaggatena "
"appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I live with a heart like fire, abundant, expansive, "
"limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an9.11:6.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa nūna, bhante, kāye kāyagatāsati anupaṭṭhitā assa, so idha aññataraṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkameyya. (3)"
msgstr ""
"Someone who had not established mindfulness of the body might well attack "
"one of their spiritual companions and leave without saying sorry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:7.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, vāyo sucimpi upavāyati asucimpi upavāyati gūthagatampi … "
"muttagatampi … kheḷagatampi … pubbagatampi … lohitagatampi upavāyati, na ca "
"tena vāyo aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose the wind was to blow on both clean and unclean things, like feces, "
"urine, spit, pus, and blood. The wind isn’t horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted because of this. …"

msgctxt "an9.11:7.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, vāyosamena cetasā viharāmi vipulena mahaggatena "
"appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I live with a heart like the wind, abundant, expansive, "
"limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an9.11:7.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa nūna, bhante, kāye kāyagatāsati anupaṭṭhitā assa, so idha aññataraṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkameyya. (4)"
msgstr ""
"Someone who had not established mindfulness of the body might well attack "
"one of their spiritual companions and leave without saying sorry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.376"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:8.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, rajoharaṇaṃ sucimpi puñchati asucimpi puñchati "
"gūthagatampi … muttagatampi … kheḷagatampi … pubbagatampi … lohitagatampi "
"puñchati, na ca tena rajoharaṇaṃ aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a rag was to wipe up both clean and unclean things, like feces, "
"urine, spit, pus, and blood. The rag isn’t horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted because of this. …"

msgctxt "an9.11:8.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, rajoharaṇasamena cetasā viharāmi vipulena "
"mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I live with a heart like a rag, abundant, expansive, "
"limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an9.11:8.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa nūna, bhante, kāye kāyagatāsati anupaṭṭhitā assa, so idha aññataraṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkameyya. (5)"
msgstr ""
"Someone who had not established mindfulness of the body might well attack "
"one of their spiritual companions and leave without saying sorry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:9.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, caṇḍālakumārako vā caṇḍālakumārikā vā kaḷopihattho "
"nantakavāsī gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā pavisanto nīcacittaṃyeva upaṭṭhapetvā "
"pavisati;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose an outcast boy or girl, holding a pot and clad in rags, were to "
"enter a town or village. They’d enter with a humble mind."

msgctxt "an9.11:9.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, caṇḍālakumārakacaṇḍālakumārikāsamena cetasā "
"viharāmi vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I live with a heart like an outcast boy or girl, abundant, "
"limitless, measureless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an9.11:9.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa nūna, bhante, kāye kāyagatāsati anupaṭṭhitā assa, so idha aññataraṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkameyya. (6)"
msgstr ""
"Someone who had not established mindfulness of the body might well attack "
"one of their spiritual companions and leave without saying sorry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:10.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, usabho chinnavisāṇo sūrato sudanto suvinīto rathiyāya "
"rathiyaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ anvāhiṇḍanto na kiñci hiṃsati pādena vā "
"visāṇena vā;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a bull with his horns cut, gentle, well tamed and well "
"trained. He’d wander from street to street and square to square without "
"hurting anyone with his feet or horns."

msgctxt "an9.11:10.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, usabhachinnavisāṇasamena cetasā viharāmi vipulena "
"mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I live with a heart like a bull with horns cut, abundant, "
"expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an9.11:10.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa nūna, bhante, kāye kāyagatāsati anupaṭṭhitā assa, so idha aññataraṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkameyya. (7)"
msgstr ""
"Someone who had not established mindfulness of the body might well attack "
"one of their spiritual companions and leave without saying sorry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.377"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:11.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍanakajātiko "
"sīsaṃnhāto ahikuṇapena vā kukkurakuṇapena vā manussakuṇapena vā kaṇṭhe "
"āsattena aṭṭīyeyya harāyeyya jiguccheyya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a woman or man who was young, youthful, and fond of "
"adornments, and had bathed their head. If the corpse of a snake or a dog or "
"a human was hung around their neck, they’d be horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted."

msgctxt "an9.11:11.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, iminā pūtikāyena aṭṭīyāmi harāyāmi jigucchāmi."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I’m horrified, repelled, and disgusted by this rotten body."

msgctxt "an9.11:11.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa nūna, bhante, kāye kāyagatāsati anupaṭṭhitā assa, so idha aññataraṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkameyya. (8)"
msgstr ""
"Someone who had not established mindfulness of the body might well attack "
"one of their spiritual companions and leave without saying sorry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:12.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, puriso medakathālikaṃ parihareyya chiddāvachiddaṃ "
"uggharantaṃ paggharantaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose someone was to carry around a bowl of fat that was leaking and "
"oozing from holes and cracks."

msgctxt "an9.11:12.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, imaṃ kāyaṃ pariharāmi chiddāvachiddaṃ uggharantaṃ "
"paggharantaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I carry around this body that’s leaking and oozing from "
"holes and cracks."

msgctxt "an9.11:12.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa nūna, bhante, kāye kāyagatāsati anupaṭṭhitā assa, so idha aññataraṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ āsajja appaṭinissajja cārikaṃ pakkameyyā”ti. (9)"
msgstr ""
"Someone who had not established mindfulness of the body might well attack "
"one of their spiritual companions and leave without saying sorry.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:13.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so bhikkhu uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhagavato "
"pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then that monk rose from his seat, placed his robe over one shoulder, bowed "
"with his head at the Buddha’s feet, and said:"

msgctxt "an9.11:13.2"
msgid ""
"“accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yo ahaṃ "
"āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ asatā tucchā musā abhūtena abbhācikkhiṃ."
msgstr ""
"“I have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of me to "
"speak ill of Venerable Sāriputta with a false, baseless, lying, untruthful "
"claim."

msgctxt "an9.11:13.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa me, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhatu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Please, sir, accept my mistake for what it is, so I will restrain myself in "
"future.”"

#. VAR: taṃ → tvaṃ (si, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.11:13.4"
msgid ""
"“Taggha taṃ, bhikkhu, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, "
"yo tvaṃ sāriputtaṃ asatā tucchā musā abhūtena abbhācikkhi."
msgstr ""
"“Indeed, monk, you made a mistake. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of "
"you to act in that way."

msgctxt "an9.11:13.5"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarosi, "
"taṃ te mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr ""
"But since you have recognized your mistake for what it is, and have dealt "
"with it properly, I accept it."

msgctxt "an9.11:13.6"
msgid ""
"Vuḍḍhihesā, bhikkhu, ariyassa vinaye yo accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ "
"paṭikaroti āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"For it is growth in the training of the noble one to recognize a mistake for "
"what it is, deal with it properly, and commit to restraint in the future.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.378"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an9.11:14.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Sāriputta:"

#. VAR: phalatī”ti → phalissatīti (si, s1, s2, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an9.11:14.2"
msgid ""
"“khama, sāriputta, imassa moghapurisassa, purā tassa tattheva sattadhā "
"muddhā phalatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sāriputta, forgive that foolish man before his head explodes into seven "
"pieces right here.”"

msgctxt "an9.11:14.3"
msgid "“Khamāmahaṃ, bhante, tassa āyasmato sace maṃ so āyasmā evamāha:"
msgstr "“I will pardon that venerable if he asks me:"

msgctxt "an9.11:14.4"
msgid "‘khamatu ca me so āyasmā’”ti."
msgstr "‘May the venerable please pardon me too.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.11:14.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
